==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*īdla-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[#Old Frisian|īdel]], Old Saxon [[idal|īdal]] (Dutch [[ijdel]] ‘unimportant’), Old High German [[ital|ītal]] (German [[eitel]] ‘bare, worthless’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈi:del/}}

